    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 is a pristine example of the FD3S chassis, featuring the sequential twin-turbocharged 13B-REW rotary powerplant. The engine maintains exceptional compression across all rotor faces, benefiting from a meticulously maintained cooling system and a simplified vacuum routing for enhanced boost response. The drivetrain is anchored by a crisp 5-speed manual gearbox and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. The suspension retains its original kinematics with refreshed bushings to sharpen the double-wishbone feedback. This vehicle exhibits zero chassis oxidation or structural fatigue, preserving the near-perfect 50:50 weight distribution that defines its handling characteristics. A true collector-grade specimen with no mechanical compromises.",
